scope_of_work.problem: Following the latest fuel condition report - 'SDM - Oct 22' it has been identified that it is necessary to increase the quantity and improve the quality of fuel stored in DRUPS 3 & 4 fuel tanks.
scope_of_work.scope:
Key info:
Each DRUPS Bulk Tank holds 26,000L
DRUPS3 Bulk Tank currently 25297L
DRUPS4 Bulk Tank currently 24162L
Request is to uplift and dispose of any unrecoverable fuel - quote to include the bottom 3000L of each DRUPS 3&4 Bulk Fuel Tanks
Blend recoverable fuel with Enzyme Energy to prevent microbial growth.
Filter recoverable fuel back into DRUPS 3&4 Bulk Fuel Tanks via 1-micron filters.
Replace DRUPS bulk tank desiccant breathers.
scope_of_work.justification: This work is required to ensure the DRUPS will continue to meet the required runtime and performance design criteria.
scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: There will become risks of poor performance resulting in the DRUPS not meeting the required design criteria for runtime and performance for providing backup to critical DC systems.

scope_of_work.problem: Generators F & H not synching and closing to the output switchboard during the Mains Fail Black Start 05.11.2022
scope_of_work.scope:
CBRE and generator specialist investigated the issue 05.11.2022 extended hours. Tripping battery unit and batteries were found to be faulty. Tripping batteries replaced. Replacement battery charger A required. Ph1A black start mains fail repeated with no issues.
UPS backed second supply wiring to the Generator A and B tripping units is a follow up recommendation and action in order to provide N+1 tripping supply
scope_of_work.justification: 24volt DC battery system required for auto changeover from Mains to Generator in the event of no mains. Dual supply tripping batteries is a best practice
scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: Reduced resilience. Design not meeting best practice

scope_of_work.problem: Pump head no.2 of dual heat pump has failed, requires complete overhaul,
scope_of_work.scope:
Contractor to Attend site to isolate and remove pump head no.2. 
Install blanking plate to leave pump set operational
Return pump head to workshop to dismantle and inspect
Supply and install the following items
Mechanical Seal
Pump Shaft
O-rings
Wear ring
Motor Bearings
Rebuild, clean and return pump to site to install
Make all mechanical and electrical connections
Test and commission
scope_of_work.justification: The dual pump assists in suppliying heating to the PH1 building, currently only pump No.1 works, Pump No.2 does not hold presure and has failed, so normally the pumps would be rotated on a weekly basis this can now not be achieved.
scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: Over the long term Pump No. 1 will be running full time and due to the increased work load of the pump this will fail causing the failure to supply heating to the building.

scope_of_work.problem: Following chiller maintenance there is remedial work required
scope_of_work.scope: Renewing all 12 Pressure Relief Valve indicator gauges that have been reported as all being faulty & in need of renewal. Whilst on site we will also renew the UPS battery back up for Chiller 3 and renew the main APC 240v SMART UPS on chiller 2
scope_of_work.justification: The PRVs are safety devices on refrigeration system to discharge excess pressure in the event of a fault. scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: In the event of a refrigerant leak it would discharge into the plant room which is hazardous to staff and equipment.

scope_of_work.problem: The diesel tank fuel line requires replacement and upgrade for metal pipe in pipe to replace the plastic section that was installed in the past as per FM Global recommendation

Disconnect temporary tank following the completion of the work
Test generator system at the end

scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: Non-compliant with FM Global recommendation and failure of the plastic pipework would lead to fuel leakage and contamination

scope_of_work.problem: Following the November 6m major generator service and load runs the OEM has observed that the air filters require replacement on the 9 sets. Air filter replacement is a MAM and based on generator hours run and visual inspections
scope_of_work.scope:
Replace generator air filters:
Ph1 - Gens 123 - 6 filters
Ph1A - Gens FGH - 6 filters
IRS - Gens ABC - 6 filters
scope_of_work.justification: Generators provide standby power to the DC in the event of Mains loss. A quality air supply is important in a generator engine's combustion process and air filters capture dirt, mold and pollen to ensure generator reliability and efficient performance
scope_of_work.non_approval_effect: Possible reduction in performance and reliability
